    • Method Detail

      • act

        public void act(SWActor a)
        Perform the Move action.

        If it is possible for SWActor a to move in the given direction, tell the world to move them and then reset a's move commands to take into account a possible new set of available Moves. If it is not possible for a to move in that direction, this method does nothing.

        This method will only be called if the SWActor a is alive

        Specified by:
        act in interface SWActionInterface
        Specified by:
        act in class SWAction
        Parameters:
        a - the SWActor who is moving

      • canDo

        public boolean canDo(SWActor a)
        Returns if or not a SWActor a can perform a Move command.

        This method returns true if and only if a is not dead.

        We assume that actors don't get movement commands attached to them unless they can in fact move in the appropriate direction. If this changes, then this method will need to be altered or overridden.

        Parameters:
        a - the SWActor doing the moving
        Returns:
        true if and only if a is not dead, false otherwise.
        See Also:
        starwars.SWActor#isDead()}
